caption: Great food and service! A little too pricey though

So so good! My brother, his girlfriend, two of my friends, and I went here for dinner this past Saturday night for the first time. Everything was so delicious! I ordered the octopus starter to share and we each got a cocktail 🍹. I ordered the squid ink pasta 🍝 as well as several sides for us to share including the broccolini, potatoes, and brussel sprouts. We all kept saying how good it was. My brother ordered the chocolate cake and my friends split the carrot cake and said it was the best they’ve had. My friend and I topped off the evening with espresso martinis and had no regrets. Definitely worth a visit!
Went for the restaurant week menu. Had to go with their regular menu with so many excellent choices. Great service from all the staff. You will enjoy the visit

Everything is so tasty.... the appetizers, meatballs, the cheese fondue ...... my steak was cooked perfectly, the sides were delicious(crispy potatoes, roasted brussel sprouts) the pasta, the wine, the desserts were all delicioso!!! Then to top it all off!!! The service is just so spot on....I love being served and pampered..... will definitely be back for more!!👍🏾

We had a temperature check and they only accepted reservations. For a friend date, we were spaced out only a little from either side of our tables. Our waiter was very attentive and suggested some good food options. My favorite was the hummus looking appetizer- SO GOOD!

Honestly not impressed, unfortunately my experience wasn’t the best. Waiter was rude and sarcastic. Food was average for the price. Chicago has far more quality Italian restaurants that would appreciate my business, I was better off dinning at Joe Imports down the street but I wanted to try something new. Service and the drinks were a deal breaker for me not to want to come back.
Love this place!

What a fantastic restaurant, the best Italian food. I brought a business associate and her family We had many appetizers and they were great We also had a pizza and it was super crispy and flavorful The green lasagna is so good We had many desserts the best was the gelato with espresso.
First time in this place great experience

Love this restaurant, amazing food & the service matches. Fernando is one of the best servers I’ve ever had & all the staff I was in contact with were great. I appreciate amazing food and service, will definitely be back.
A bit overpriced  but  excellent food

This is a really authentic Italian eatery everyone's food was beyond excellent Scallops, Grilled Giant Prawns, and Brick chicken add small portions of Bucatini, Canestri and Giant beans of course preceded by Calamari Tempura, Grilled Octopus and Pancetta Cream Mussels made this an extravagant affair. Service was top shelf including a Sommelier's advice on wine selection.

Expensive average food. I was reading all the reviews,  and seemed promising. Sides were good, main dishes was OK. Simple food , overpriced. Chicken parm was a $40 dish that want worth $10.  You take simple dish and charge so much it's have to be good. Unfortunate.
Over all amazing, food was delicious, covid ready and the wait time was really short, will come back for sure.
Italian food, mmm, delicious. prices were fair.
Outdoor greenhouses are extremely warm! Food is overall delicious with big portions.
My favorite location for quality Italian food. It's so appetizing. I'll return with my coworkers. Not close to my job, I wish it was.
Great food and service.

What I loved - Burrata was great, Brussel sprouts were 😋, cacio e pepe and spaghetti with Chicken parmesan was juicy and flavorful.  Chocolate cake and Tiramisu were awesome. Service was exemplary!  What I didn't care for - The heated tents were insufficiently heated and there was a windy draft that was bothersome so I recommend dressing super warm (pants and footwear) and carrying some hand and foot warmers to stay comfortable for the 90min or so you dine there.
The food was delicious, atmosphere delightful, and service impeccable.

Husband made reservations at Formento’s for New Years Eve, one of the few places that offered indoor dining. Felt like a high end restaurant on first impression but the waiters wearing hoodies/casual clothing and dining area suggested otherwise. Got 2 pcs of complimentary bread with oil which was like any other Italian restaurant, nothing special. For starters we ordered: Whipped Ricotta, Frito Misto and Cauliflower. Whipped Ricotta was the best starter out of the 3, Frito Misto was salty but still edible, Cauliflower was wayy too salty that we were not able to finish it. For main meal we ordered the Risotto and Orecchiette. Risotto tasted like seafood Mac and cheese for children. Do not recommend. Orecchiette was like buttered noodles with shrimp, nothing special. Overall, prices were too high for the food and we will not be back here.
absolutely loved it, ambiance was so pretty, the food was amazing everyone was so sweet and nice. My sister and I tasted each other's food and it's sooo good. We are definitely going back!
Hemingway Daiquiri and Whipped Ricotta!!!
Delicious food (had the bucatini and brussel sprouts on the side), service was fantastic, and the tent was warm enough to be comfortable and open enough to feel safe. I'll definitely be back!
Every dish we ordered was amazing. Their wine recommendations were perfect to our taste. Food was just aweaome. They are very friendly and have excellent service.
Great place making the best of COVID restrictions.  The food was amazing
Delicious & the igloos outside were comfy and warm with the space heaters going on a chilly December evening. Great attentive staff who know the menu and wine list extremely well.

We came for date night and sat in their outdoor tent. We felt very safe and perfectly comfortable! The service was wonderful, though it was a little loud. We had the kale salad and cauliflower to start. The cauliflower was recommended by our server and it had a good range of flavors, but wasn't as crispy as I was hoping. I got the bucatini and my fiance got the risotto. My bucatini was cold and the noodles stuck together. I also wish the pieces of bacon were smaller and the egg yolk was mixed in (though it did look beautiful this way!). The risotto was incredible! Nice and spicy and the seafood was delicious! The piece of carrot cake we had for dessert was underwhelming. I would love to come back another time and try some other items on the menu!
Great food, great price for the portions the staff was very nice service was fast an the atmosphere was wonderful
Great place, good food...very creatively decorated....friendly service…
Awesome place to eat alone or with family and friends. Attentive staff, delicious food, and worth a visit!

Great dinner. Excellent service (in these days of Covid) staff goes above & beyond to keep everyone safe. Food was excellent.  Outdoor tent (again, Covid) well ventilated and heated. Can't imagine what could possibly have been better. 👍👍👍👍
Good service and food. But I was expecting something better considering the price of their meals.
Came for dinner over the past week. Servers were very friendly, heaters were warm (a key right now!), and food was great. Also, solid wine selection.
Best Italian in west loop! Amazing staff!
The food was nice but Paulina our server was terrific and made us feel like the old days before Auntie Rona ruin it.  Side note the noodle with the egg yolk was amazing
Great service. Great food. We were spaced comfortably apart from other parties while eating indoors. They also offered a complimentary air purifier for the table which was pretty neat.
What a nice restaurant, mussels were amazing delicious

Went last night and was super impressed by the presentation and taste of each course. I would recommend the canestri 6oz. The portion was perfect and the pasta itself was delectable. My tables service was spot on and Jeff was attentive to all our needs. It’s a tad bit overpriced if I’ll be honest, but it’s still delicious food.
Great spot for a steak... Pasta was on point thanks guys
Italian food, mmm, very tasty.
Food was good but not exceptional, with lovely service. The mascarpone cherry gelato was ridiculously good.
I wouldn’t say this is the best Italian food I’ve had in Chicago, but not bad overall. Food was fresh and tasty. Environment was very good.
The food and the service are excellent! Their dishes are great! They have unique Italian dishes you do not find anywhere else.
My favorite Italian restaurant in Chicago. The pasta is ridiculously good.
Italian food and the scene at this place is great. Fell in love with this place from the 1st taste. The service was sociable and attentive. Bring your hunger - portions are large.
Delicious food and nice staff!
Excellent food
Everything we ate, which was a lot, was amazing and everyone that worked there was great, so nice and knowledgeable. Plus the outside seating set-up was very comfortable for distancing now.
Fine Italian dining with plenty of outdoor seating on Randolph St. Loved the Squid Ink Orecchiette with rock shrimp!
Delicious food. Excellent service.  Very good COVID procedures. We felt safe and had a great time.
Big portions, fresh food, and everything I've ever eaten from here has been extremely delicious. Definitely recommend.

My friend and I ate here and the food was amazing! One of the best carbonaras I have ever eaten. The service was excellent and the overall experience was elevated, yet still casual. Would definitely recommend!
Fantastic pastas (the carbonara is just simply heavenly) and their desserts, especially the Nonna’s tiramisu, are outstanding as well. Definitely recommend. The delivery experience was great, too.
The best calamari in town (and it’s gluten free!!) amazing gluten free pasta too.
Too expensive small portions!!
Carbonara!!
(Translated by Google) Rigato !!  (Original) Rigato!!
Man the food was delicious. I forgot the name of it but  I had a pasta in tomato sauce with a neck bone gravy over meat balls and sausage with a glass of wine.

Great place with good outdoor seating that has kept their excellent food and service despite Covid. Where other restaurants slack off this one always delivers in quality of food, service and atmosphere. Can’t say enough about the elegance and professionalism of the staff and the manager.
I would gladly go back to this place and explore their menu once more!
Delicious meal with excellent staff. Mr. Arturo was really friendly and extremely knowledgeable about the city.
Food was great, and West Loop location was fun.
Food and service were solid.  Good Italian wine list.  Parking is rough.

Last night I went to this place and is delicious!!!
Excellent Italian, the Veal Chop was outstanding!
It was delicious and the service was awesome!! I highly recommend the calamari and the lamb chops.
Great staff, great drinks, decent atmosphere.  But the prices are way over the top for the portions you get.  The papperdelle was swimming in butter.  Kinda gross.
The pasta was amazing as well as the steak. They are accommodating with food allergies. Our server Murphy was amazing, so attentive.
Great food!
Nice :)

Delicious food, good portions. Cauliflower starter was amazing!
Great Italian food

Ah yes it's restaurant week in Chicago, and Formento's did well.  The cacio I Pepe bucatini was lovely, the multitude of courses left one feeling full and the value with restaurant week was excellent.  The GEM salad was better than the meatballs.  Don't get me wrong the meatballs were good but the selection of produce for the salad was exquisite.  The butcher steak was tasty as well, not quite truly Italian but it worked well Leith the whole presentation.  Service was on point and the wine pairing went well with the courses.  Dessert cake was good but I was too full to appreciate.  We had to wait for 15 minutes past our reservation but the waitress made up with some burrata and olives as a complimentary lagniappe.  Overall I was pleased.
Excellent service!! Anter and Josh know their bourbon. Josh made a perfect Old Fashioned, best I’ve ever had. Go, you won’t be disappointed.

Our party was anticipating a lovely evening, based on reviews; very disappointing. Food was a "D" for price point at best, slow service,  and arrogant attitude. I tried to follow up with GM following dinner, he could care less, no follow up. So many better options in Chicago!
Everything was deliciousband freshly made. Formento's is indeed one of the best!

Visited Formento's for dinner and the only thing better than the service was the food.  Our server, Murphy, perfectly paired a glass of wine for each of our 3 courses. Everything we ate was delicious and filling, make sure to bring a second stomach for dessert!

We were served by Chloe. Very friendly and helpful. We felt very accommodated. Thank you. Also we arrived 10 mins before kitchen closed because we were too late for our reservation. But we still got our ourdinner. Awesome and all of them were great. Thanks a lot. Highly recommended
Pasta is solid. A bit pricey for portions
SO VERY DELICIOUS!!!!  Our waiter was Abel and he was GREAT!!!! The food was so very very delicious!  It met and exceeded all expectations.
Apps were good but steak wasn't that great. Forgot to make my friend's drink but comped it

Really enjoyed every bit of it. Stopped by alone for a quick Italian bit but ended up killing a full course meal with three drinks! Special thanks to my server Jeff for all the best recommendations. Would definitely kove to visit with more friends next time.
Great service!!
Not an expert on Italian food but truly enjoyed their Strozzapreti. You can see in the photo the dish is covered in a crumb of some sort which added really good texture to the shrimp and noodles.
Service is tops. And the selection of pasta dishes is imaginative...and delicious. And for Fulton Market, the prices were reasonable.

Best restaurant in the West Loop. You could find your favorite and discover new cuisine. Atmosphere n service is 👍. This is a great place to dine solo. But best place to impress your company/guest/people u know
I recommend the gigli pasta
Nice restaurant
Great service and great food.
Great food! Great atmosphere! Love Formento's!
Avocado toast is a must. The meatball app is too. Loved the chocolate cake. Staff is on the top of their game.

Perhaps the best brussels sprouts I have eaten and the steak was cooked to perfection and nicely seasoned. Would have been a slam dunk five star, but an Italian restaurant running out of Peroni was most unexpected.
Subpar food for twice the price.
Really good food and great for large groups. Overall really tasty.
Food was good but not impressed, particularly for the price point.
Average Italian food

Went there with some colleagues to take out a visiting speaker, so wanted something nice, and local. I figure it’s a bit pricey but the food was very good and the service was excellent- must have had at least 5 staff taking care of 4 of us at different times. Fancy wine list, lots of options for shared plates, plus a selection of individual mains. I’m not the hugest fan of whole artichokes, but theirs is truly excellent. Calamari was good, too. I had the scallops - delicious and not heavy. Our guest had the huge NY steak, and we ordered broccolini as a side (yum). Another in the party had the squid ink pasta. We shared a dessert - chocolate cake - OMG. If you love good food, enjoy Italian fare and have something to celebrate or someone to impress, it’s probably a solid choice.
Second positive experience. Flavorful, well-prepared food. High marks for the meatballs and scallops! Friendly service, but too attentive, making us feel hurried.

We held a wedding rehearsal dinner for a party of 50 in the spacious second floor "Ballroom" private area of this wonderful Italian restaurant on West Randolph. Ashlei and Monica are great to work with in planning an event, and Antar did a great job executing the service during our four-hour event. Their website has a downloadable "event packet" that displays the numerous bar and food options for an event. We chose a "family style" option - which allowed our guests to experience a variety of appetizer and entree options.
Wonderful wait staff and excellent food.  Had a wonderful evening.
Wonderful brunch and service. The Jumbo Lump Crab Benedict and Whipped Ricotta were excellent!
Great foods
We attended a wedding here and it was beautiful. Plus the cake (which is from the menu) was just to die for. I almost asked for a second slice 🍰
Attentive service, delicious meal (bucatini and ribeye), a bit pricey for Italian.
Great Italian in the West loop. Small plates to share for great variety. Try the meatballs for sure.

Amazing food, one of the best italian restaurants I've ever had the pleasure of enjoying. Must try the Bucatini, the paparedelle is phenomenal. The pasta is made fresh daily and it is heavenly!

Excellent service. Great tasting dishes. Definitely worth another visit!

This was my first time here and lets just say that I will be coming back over and over! The food was incredible and the service was impeccable! Delaney our waitress, made our first time experience wonderful!
We only had drinks but loved the ambiance upstairs

Food was wonderful and had a nice old school Italian atmosphere with great ambiance.  The waitstaff were great and very informative for our group of first timers.  However our only issue was with the 4-5 hostess staff we encountered this past Sat. evening.  Very rude and pretentious!!  Our party of four were not impressed in the least with the snooty attitude and treatment from  the group behind the desk.  We were "penalized" for missing the 15 minute reservation window by 3 minutes due to an unknown local parade blocking traffic for our uber driver.   The girls behind the desk chastised us for being late then we were made to stand next to the open booth we were told we would be seated at for 13 minutes.  Seemed to be a punishment for some reason?? There was no reason to make us stand other than to "shame" us and make us feel "thankful" to at least get a booth since our reservation had been "canceled" due to our 3 minute late arrival.  Needless to say we almost left due but based on a great waitstaff response and the idea of great Italian food we saw it through and had a great evening.  I can't however honestly say I would go back however due to the  pretentious treatment we received.  It was embarrassing and I'd rather spend my hard earned money at a place that appreciate's it!
It was decent but overrated imo
Outstanding
I celebrated my 30th birthday at Formento's Great atmosphere! Amazing staff and vibe. Will definitely be going again!

Excellent spot. Grab a reservation for 6:45. Arrive at 6pm for happy hour at the bar. I recommend the calamari and meatball as happy hour appetizers. The old fashion is great. And then enjoy the dinner reservation. Cant go wrong with the bucatini or canestri.
Great place and food with exceptional service!

Great gem in West Loop. Came with my fiance for a Thursday night dinner date. Cozy ambiance with a home feel with the exposed brick. Started with the Ricotta cheese app, and the dish was super creamy with some very nicely toasted bread. Added a gnocchi and lamb chops along with some red Tuscan wine. Delicious and fun night out!

What a great place! Just came for the second time and was even more impressed than the first! Had a large party and everyone loved it! It’s a must visit! The best food, first class service and second to none options! Highly highly recommend!!

I had a wonderful experience here... the food was splendid and the service was great. It is a classy, intimate atmosphere serving a mix of new world and old world italian dishes. I had the artichoke which was wood fired giving it a delicious smoky flavor. The calamari was fried in a unique batter that made it very crispy with a spicy aioli. The seasonal mozzarella salad with honey crisp apples and grapes was unique and delicious!! For my entree I ordered the infamous bucatini carbonara and it did not disappoint!!! The pasta is made fresh and was absolutely delicious. They house cure their pancetta and the presentation of this dish is awesome. Definitely recommend. And don't leave without trying their signature hazelnut chocolate cake!!!! It's to die for!

On a tip from local colleagues had dinner here on a warm night. Outdoor patio seating was perfect. Service was efficient and friendly. Everything we had (three of us) was excellent and included made to order non dairy requirements. Highlight was a risotto with lobster—perfectly prepared (not an easy thing to do) and perfect portion size. Highly recommended for a nice night out—nice wine list too!
Are 4 mentose enough mentose? I still haven't gotten to the bottom of this question. Their food is pretty good but for the price I would expect better.
Amazing food
Great pasta dishes
Great food and service! The salmon was excellent.
The bartender was fantastic  very attentive I believe his name was Joshua
Very nice option for upscale Italian in the  West Loop. An appropriate number of dishes for all tastes (pasta, seafood, meats) and a eclectic wine list. Service was great as well.
Jesus Mora is the best waiter there hands down. The staff in general is fantastic. I would give the menu 1000+ stars if I could. The environment is electric. Recommend everyone to go here.
Great ambiance ... just sat at the bar.  Olives app is great!!
Amazing food and great table service
Great service.
Hands down one of the very best Italian meals I have ever had in Chicago!!  Excellent menu, great wine list, and super attentive service.  Loved everything about it!!
Great Italian food.
Great food and awesome environment!
Excellent food and friendly and attentive staff
The pasta was okay. Drinks are good. Apps were good as well. We didn’t try the steak.
Uninspiring pappardelle at a high price. Glasses of wine at bottle prices. Chocolate cake seemed store bought.

This is hands down one of the best restaurants in the city. The two times I've been here, I've ordered the exact same thing. Nonna's meatballs, bucatini, and the chocolate cake.  The meatballs are a great dish to share, and and perfectly tender and juicy. The bucatini is definitely one of my favorite pasta dishes. The noodles are cooked to perfection, and the sauce and toppings are simple but strong in flavor. As with the other pasta dishes, you can get a half order instead of a full order, which is what I got, and I still left feeling very full.  The chocolate cake is TO DIE FOR!!! It is quite literally the best slice of cake I have ever had. And this is coming from someone who doesn't like chocolate. There are so many layers to this cake, and each layer showcases a different texture of chocolate, so there's crispiness in it, ganache, cream, sponge cake, and so on. Just so, so good. You cannot miss it if you come here.  Lastly, service and ambiance were impeccable. You can come with two people or ten and the service team will make it a great time for you. I came with a group of six last time, and the server was great in accommodating all of our needs.
Great pasta

Went on a Saturday night and it was the best food we’ve had on our trip. Everything was delicious and so meticulously created and presented. Service was fantastic and we had the perfect amount of attention from our waiter, Sommelier, and support staff without being overbearing or overwhelming.  We had the swordfish special of the evening, the butcher steak, ravioli, mussels and meatballs. Every dish was splendid and paired brilliantly with the bottle of wine our sommelier chose.  Overall we were incredibly impressed and will certainly be back again!
Absolutely wonderful!! Thank you Charles and Murphy!!
Smelled weird, cant get past places smelling weird.
Wonderful food, great service.
Outstanding experience!! The service was excellent and the food was delicious. I was here last year and could not wait to come back.

The pasta is good. I don't know why they'd compare themselves to anything "old world" "red sauce" Italian... Because it isn't. The gelato is tasty. The service is good. There are better, less expensive, Italian joints in the city.

Quaint Italian in the west loop. The Veal parm and the service were excellent. We had a group of 11, and i think the only downside was the rather limited drink menu options as opposed to what you typically find in Chicago.
Pricey, but very good

I have to thank Formento's, especially the front of house staff, for our experience today. While we did not dine there they allowed me to bring in our recently toilet trained child when he was having an emergency on our walk.  They hurried to show us the facilities, congratulated us after with high fives, and gave my child a small prize. We will definitely patronize them in the near future.   ¡Gracias!

We had a great time at Formento's, and found a favorite Italian restaurant for the next time we are in Chicago! We came late in the evening, sat at the bar and had the delight of being served by Pam. The food here is excellent, but Pam definitely made our night even more enjoyable with top-notch customer service. We were thoroughly impressed with the attention to detail that was given to each drink being made throughout our 2 hour stay, and this attention to detail and enthusiasm is reflected across the entire restaurant and was seen in every staff member that assisted us this evening. The highlights of our evening were the mussels (cooked perfectly, but the combination of the cream in the sauce with all of the bacon and lemon flavor made us ask for extra bread because of the all the flavor), the ricotta ravioli (again, the flavor with the lemon and mushrooms and the texture of the sauce were perfect accompanists to the pasta), the coconut tapioca pudding and the sorbet float.  If you're in the West Loop, definitely give Formento's a try!
Great food
The menu was rather small but the food was rather amazing.  The wine list on the other hand is IMMENSE and the Rioja we had was to die for.
One of my favorite spots in the city! The bucatini is addictive 😋
The food was great, specially the shared plates and pastas. Staff were really friendly and we were lucky to get a table for 10 outside on the quite side of the building. Over all a great experience.

It was good. The company was better. I enjoy tasting new things. Would have recieved 5 stars if I knew that my order would double in price as the pasta is listed at a certain price point but not considered entree portion size.

Italian restaurant and bar.  I asked bartender Pamela for a spicy mixed drink and she whipped me up a custom spicy tequila drink she made up on the spot!  she callled it "hot n fuzzy".  it smelled amazing with a sweet citrus aroma.  it tasted very refreshing.  as expected it was mildly spicy with a semi sweet citrus flavor.  dinner was amazing too. appetizers tried were calamari, cauliflower, zucchini, meatballs, pasta with pork and red cauce.
Service wasn’t the quickest but the fresh pasta was delicious.
I absolutely love this place!  I have been here several times with my family and it is always a wonderful experience.
Amazing food and service!
I had a wonderful brick chicken dinner here, we sat in the room with one of the largest round banquettes I had ever seen. The crowd was fun and carefree, the food and service very good.
The kitchen was more then willing to make accommodations for all and the food was amazing.

Had dinner with work. I had the lamb, which was delicious. I think for what’s on offer, they’re a bit too pricey - hence 4 instead of 5 stars - but loved the atmosphere. We were seated at a round-ish table, and I loved that. Great bar in the upfront area.
Great patio seating, awesome service!
Good classic Italian favorites
The food was absolutely fantastic, the service was top notch and the place had a great vibe altogether.  They have a nice bar area too.
Nice patio seating
Great food. Nice ambiance
Business dinner at this place and everything was done right, courteous staff. Everyone enjoyed
Liked their brunch
Food is consistently good, busser staff was amazing, server was a little forgetful but the others made up for it. One of my fave places on randolph.
Just go here. You will not be disappointed

One of my favorite restaurants in the city! Great choice for a girls dinner, date night, family meal, or group celebration. Very spacious inside which I love so you don't feel like you're bumping elbows with your neighbors or having to shout to be heard. If the weather is nice you should sit outside on their charming patio. Thoughtful seasonal food that's executed at a high level. Knowledgeable, friendly, attentive service from the entire team starting with the hostess to the server and the runners. Love that they started offering delivery too.  My recommendations: -CALAMARI WITH PEPPERONCINI AIOLI. Who doesn't love fried calamari?! The pepperoncini aioli is awesome and I want to dip everything in it. -BUCATINI CARBONARA. No words...just order this. adjacent Nonna's. The fennel sausage is fantastic too. -SCALLOPS. I’ve had the winter preparation and the most recent spring version with barley, spring vegetables, and pea puree and every time, the flavors and execution of the dish have been wonderful. -CRISPY CAULIFLOWER WITH PEPPERONI, GREEN CHILES, LEMON. Best veggie side dish/appetizer! The chiles give a nice kick and the lemon add brightness. -CHOCOLATE CAKE WITH DARK CHOCOLATE MOUSSE AND HAZELNUT PRALINE. Without a doubt the best chocolate cake. Period. This is the cake I want to devour on my birthday...or any day. It's outstanding.  Next visit I want to try the VEAL PARMESAN or the CHICKEN PARMESAN I’ve been seeing people rave about on social media! It looks amazing.
A complete experience.  Outstanding service coupled with exceptional appetizers,  salads and main courses.  An extensive wine list and reasonably priced adds to the experience.  Highly recommended.
The Bucatini and the Ribeye.....👏👏👏👏👏
Delaney and the food was amazing!
Appetizers and pasta are good. Ordered a steak and was very disappointed.  Tough and grisley and poor flavor. Service was friendly but a bit slow

My family and I went here for my Birthday dinner before a big show at the United Center. Service was incredible, the food was outstanding, and I had a very special surprise visit from the Chef/Owner, Todd Stein. He gave us one dessert on the house. That was one Birthday I will never forget. I will definitely come back here again for special occasions, and I will definitely recommend this restaurant for fans of Italian cuisine.
Great food and fun atmosphere
Really great vibe and nice bar area.  The veal parmesan was a huge chop so you won't go hungry.  My friend and I also loved our salad.  I thought it was a little expensive for 2 people.

The best carbonara I have ever had hands down. And not only was the food delicous but the service puts to shame many other Chicago restaurants. I never had to flag down a waiter all evening. They set the bar high for Italian food and service in Chicago.

We happened upon here by chance and our whole group (shocking to please everyone) were amazed, happy, and satisfied. Great, awesome, respectful service (thank you Jesus M) made sure we were enjoying what turned out to be a bunch of new meal and drink and dessert options! Best experience in Chicago.  Until the menu changes I strongly suggest the Rhubarb dessert. Magnificently prepared and served.
I had rather not go into details but they have the best customer service
Very poor, calamari so, Greasy. One meatball served in a paper box. Pass on this one
The food was delious and fresh, our waitress was friendly and great at her job, the look and feel of the resturant was top notch. Will be coming back.

The food was ok, though had some issues, see below, but where it lacked the most was in service. My wife and I just went there for brunch and both were quite underwhelmed.  Mascarpone marmalade toast was smothered with a ludicrous amount of marmalade.. sticky fingers and a 1/4 cup scooped off was the result.  And the Kale salad was slathered in dressing, that was good, but too much of anything good  will ruin even a great salad. Yes in retrospect, dressing should have been ordered on the side (my mistake) but I presumed that the salad would not be served swimming in dressing.  Bringing it (salad  of and over marmaladed toast situation) to the attention of our waiter   in the pretty empty place today -who spent more time socializing with the staff rather than stopping at our table more often, resulted in a ''I will mention it to the kitchen' remark.  Mistakes, blurred with misunderstandings, happen all the time at every restaurant, and  what separates ok places from the best, is service. Being observant and listening to patrons is how you keep people coming back.  Our waiter never stopped  by to ask how the meal was after being served, did not notice  low coffee cups (had to ask each time for a refill), did not ask or offer to remedy a complaint,  did  not realize that perhaps particialy eaten plates are often not a sign of a happy customer- when bringing  the bill (nor asking asking if it was ok), and when walking out, the two greeters smiling at us as we walked out did not ask how our brunch was... all these things tell me that somebody running Formento's is not schooling the wait staff how to listen to and observe when restaurant patrons are not happy.

I have been wanting to come here for a long time, and was finally able to go this week for a client dinner- WOW. How come this doesn’t get more hype?! Everything was wild with flavor and unique. We got the meatballs, broccolini and focaccia bread to start. Then shared two orders of the bucatini and the agnolotti. My gosh... they both were to die for. You HAVE to try the bucatini. The egg yolk at first freaked me out, but it tastes like decadent Mac and cheese when it’s all mixed in together. I got the lamb chops for my main course! They had great flavor, but were very fatty. However, this was a very minor set back compared to the overall experience. I texted my boyfriend after and asked if he wanted to go again soon! Can’t wait to try again!

This restaurant is extremely beautiful and has wonderful service and food. The moment I walked in one server told me my shirt was beautiful and instantly heightened my mood. When it came out it might’ve been the most flavorful appetizers I’ve ever had in my life, it was fantastic. When we started to order our main dishes Our server told us about their most famous dishes and what drinks to pair them with because of the flavor combinations, we got the bucatini carbonara and the fusilli. Another server had come over to our table after we had ordered our main dish  and said that the lady who is serving us was a trainee! It was As if she had completely blended into the rest of the staff! The other server who came over to our table also helped the table next to us and we overheard the level of Extreme detail she used when describing wines for the other people to drink. Overall this experience was fantastic and I would definitely recommend it for anyone who wants good Italian food!! 10/10

Formento's, I've always loved you, but now I love you even more! I am gluten and dairy free, which for most begs the question of why I would even step foot in an Italian restaurant. But, tonight you didn't just "accommodate me", you made me feel VALUED and WELCOME. And for that I can't thank you enough compared to the many times other places have made me feel like an inconvenience. I come to gobble up your amazing GF fried calamari, which is by far the best fried calamari in the city, even compared to the non-GF versions that I remember so fondly. So light and crispy and tender...and half price at happy hour! It's a no brainer. Tonight when my friend ordered bread and olive oil...you brought me a cup of assorted olives to enjoy. And before I could even order the calamari I was craving, my server told me about your house made GF pasta. So, I excitedly ordered that, too. But you didn't just bring me the regular serving of spaghetti or penne noodles...you brought me these fun rooster noodle shapes that I've never even seen before. It sounds silly...but these fun rooster noodle shapes made me feel special. They said that you wanted me to enjoy my food experience, just like everyone else. Thank you so much for putting so much thought and effort into my GF/dairy free experience. It means the world to me to have a safe, comfortable, fun, and delicious neighborhood restaurant to enjoy. I will recommend you to everyone and come back many times over - not only for your great food, but for your top notch family style service, and above all your heart!

I'll start off saying we were able to walk right in on a Monday evening with no reservations. Found free parking across the street. Great location. Nice ambiance. Wine/Cocktail selection was good. But these are the ONLY reasons for the 2 stars.  There were 4 of us seated and we chose Formentos after  looking for an Italian place into the area. Our waiter was nice, but he teetered on the pleasant/unpleasant line. He was loud. Overenthusiastic. And simply talked too much. He was attempting to set a mood and we played along, but sometimes you know when it's forced and not genuine. He raved about the new menu. But we didn't need to be sold, we were already sitting with drinks in hand.  Now on to the food:  Whipped Ricotta - It was okay. The bread is great though. Calamari - Recommended. Cauliflower- Recommended. Rigatoni - Pasta was heavy. Not recommended. Agnolotti - The vegetarian of the group recommends. Brick Chicken - The presentation was horrible. Ill colored sauce. Randomly placed peas. 3 petite potatoes. And chicken that looked like it hadn't touch a brick or oven. The waiter described this in a way we were expecting and nicely cooked half chicken with crispy skin and juicy meat.  It wasn't a half chicken and there was no crisp to the skin. The sauce was awful and the weird smokiness flavor was confusing and didn't pair well with anything. Not at all recommended. Potatoes side dish was better - A bit of a kick. Recommended. Broccolini and Asparagus - The flavor combinations or seasonings were way off. Nothing lemon about the broccolini. And if the asparagus were cooked on wood, it was a 2x4 out back.  If you want Italian. This isn't the place. We're in Chicago and you can go to many other places for better food.
